Name: Description
Graduation Rate: New York City public high school students who graduated as of June after four years or six years of instruction. Six-year graduation rate data represent graduation rates for the cohort entering 6 years prior to the current school year (e.g. the 2019 six-year graduation rate reflect data for the 2013 cohort).

Name: Source Notes
Graduation Rate: New York City Department of Education, Graduation Results (School Years 2004-05 to 2018-19); retrieved from https://infohub.nyced.org/reports-and-policies/citywide-information-and-data/graduation-results

Name: Notes
Graduation Rate:
Data represent outcomes by graduation year. In order to comply with FERPA regulations on public reporting of education outcomes, breakdowns where the number of students in the cohort is 5 or less are suppressed and maps and tables display "no data" or "0". CCC used school-level
results to aggregate data to the community-district level.
